{Enrico Paoli (1908-2005) was the grand old man of Italian chess. He had been
a ship captain for Lloyd Triestino and learned many languages on his voyages.
Later he became the ideal organiser of international chess tournaments in
Reggio Emilia. The New Year's tournament or 'Torneo di Capodanno' started in
1958/59. Play began after Christmas and ended the next year. The budget of the
first installment was 198,000 liras. Count Giancarlo Dal Verme, president of
the Italian Chess Federation, took care of deficits in the Capodanno events.} 
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Be7 8. Qf3
O-O 9. O-O-O Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. e5 $5 {
Paoli delivers an important novelty. He starts a number of sacrifices.} dxe5
13. Qh3 {14.Bxf6 and mate is threatened.} h6 14. Bxh6 $1 gxh6 15. Qxh6 e4 $6 (
15... Rd8 $5 {will be played in furure games.}) 16. Nxe4 $6 (16. Bxe4 $1 Rd8
17. Rdf1 $1 Qd6 18. Bd3 {strengthens the attack.}) 16... Nxe4 17. Bxe4 f5 18.
